			   <h1 class="shead-style text-center">UTTRAKHAND</h1>
        <p>There it stands a land high in the mountains which has been there for thousand years. A land which is Devbhoomi for the Hindus,a land holy as the purest form of nature. Having one of the four sacred Dhams of Hindu mythology and having many sacred and historical sites Uttarakhand is definitely the retreat someone must receive within their lifetime. Comprised mostly of mountains it has many astounding and quiet places for one to visit and to have glimpse of the Himalayas.<p>
        <p>
        It also has some wildlife sanctuaries which provided shelters to many endangered and vulnerable animals. Uttrakhand which is a paradise for mountaineers and trekkers receives a large number of visitors every year from all corners of the world. Most of the mountain region is almost inaccessible due to its position and cold climate. For most part of the year it experiences a cold climate. Although most of the landscape is very scenic and astounding it’s not accessible for the most part.
        </p>
				
